README.md:22:Zero network and zero LLM calls on every CLI path ‚Äî enforced structurally by an import-graph eval, not by promise. A desktop web console (`npm run dev`: `/report`, `/demo`) renders the same machine reports in two registers, plain words first.
README.md:26:Everything asserted here is measured under committed, tamper-locked evaluation:
README.md:29:- **Eval-locks.** Every live run's raw results are frozen into the repo, and committed lock tests recompute the headline numbers from the per-item records forever ‚Äî the grade cannot be quietly edited, and "just run it again" cannot replace what happened.
README.md:30:- **Anti-theater baselines.** An LLM component must beat a pinned deterministic baseline on held-out gold before its label counts; ties lose.
README.md:31:- **Structural $0 enforcement.** Import-graph evals prove the CLI, demo, delivery builders, and web views cannot reach an LLM or the network ‚Äî not a promise, a failing test.
README.md:32:- **Frozen corpus and goldens.** Fixtures are seeded and freeze-locked (regenerate ‚áí bytes must match); reports byte-compare against goldens.
README.md:52:| Test suite | `npm run verify` green: **1001 passed + 7 skipped** (the skips are live-network harnesses, off by default; count re-measured live 2026-07-10 after the S2 honesty-contract tests landed) |
README.md:59:| Corpus | Seeded, deterministic, freeze-locked (regenerate ‚áí bytes must match); every fixture taxonomy-keyed; publishable under this repo's license |
README.md:78:Dated source records for these claims live in `docs/research/` (source lockfile included).
docs/prompt-intake-protocol.md:21:4. **Proportionality (anti-bloat ‚Äî this project's documented #1 failure mode):** **default lightweight** ‚Äî do the intent-capture *silently* and proceed. **Surface** the structured interpretation (or a confirm question) only when the request is **ambiguous or consequential** (scope ¬∑ architecture ¬∑ tools ¬∑ data ¬∑ AI behavior ¬∑ public claims ¬∑ security ¬∑ cost ¬∑ anything irreversible). Do **not** echo a formatted prompt block on a trivial request ("fix the typo") ‚Äî that is friction-theater the owner will come to hate.
